? What did John B. Watson and Rosalie Rayner demonstrate in the 1920 Little Albert experiment?
[A]* That emotional responses like fear can be classically conditioned in humans
[B] That infants can distinguish their mother's voice from birth
[C] That children learn aggression by observing adult behavior
[D] That early attachment to a caregiver is critical for social development
